.TH "snd_pcm_suspend_all" 9 "snd_pcm_suspend_all" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_suspend_all \- trigger SUSPEND to all substreams in the given pcm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_suspend_all
.BI "(struct snd_pcm *pcm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
the PCM instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
After this call, all streams are changed to SUSPENDED state.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful (or \fIpcm\fP is NULL), or a negative error code.
